	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Because Game Boy hardware prior to GBC doesn't have background tile flipping, perfect symmetry is useful only as a ROM-saving compression measure. Also on the original green-screen Game Boy, fine details of moving objects may disappear.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
